    <h2>Calculator Basis</h2>

    <p>The basis of this calculator are the following facts:</p>

    <ul id="fact-list" name="fact-list">
      <li><span class="site-item">Fact:</span> The <em>Next Generation</em> episode <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Neutral_Zone_(Star_Trek:_The_Next_Generation)">"The Neutral Zone"</a>, with a stardate of 41986.0, gave the calendar year as 2364 at the end of the first season.</li>
      <li><span class="site-item">Fact:</span> In the <em>Voyager</em> episode <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eye_of_the_Needle_(Star_Trek:_Voyager)" name="episode">"Eye of the Needle"</a> Commander Chakotay states that the current year is 2371, with a stardate of 48579.4.</li>
      <li><span class="site-item">Fact:</span> The date for the <em>Voyager</em> episode <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/11:59_(Star_Trek:_Voyager)" name="episode">"11:59"</a> was given as 22 April 2375. (No stardate was given in the episode, but episodes airing before and after it had stardates of 52647 and 52861.274.)</li>
      <li><span class="site-item">Fact:</span> The movie <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Star_Trek:_First_Contact" name="movie"><em>Star Trek: First Contact</em></a> showed that humans made first contact with Vulcans on 5 April 2063.</li>
      <li><span class="site-item">Fact:</span> In the <em>Voyager</em> episode <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Homestead_(Star_Trek:_Voyager)" name="episode">"Homestead"</a> the crew is celebrating the 315th anniversary of First Contact Day. The following day, a captain's log is recorded on stardate 54868.6.</li>
      <li><span class="site-item">Fact:</span> In the <em>Voyager</em> episode <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Q2_(Star_Trek:_Voyager)" name="episode">"Q2"</a>, Icheb states that Kirk completed his historic five-year mission in 2270. Therefore, all episodes of The Original Series must have taken place after 1 January 2265 (assuming it was exactly five years), and before 1 January 2271.</li>
      <li><span class="site-item">Fact:</span> In the <em>Next Generation</em> episode <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sarek_(Star_Trek:_The_Next_Generation)" name="episode">"Sarek"</a>, Captain Picard states that Ambassador Sarek is 202 years old. The episode takes place on stardate 43917.4.</li>
      <li><span class="site-item">Fact:</span> In the <em>Original Series</em> episode <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Journey_to_Babel" name="episode">"Journey to Babel"</a>, Ambassador Sarek states that he is precisely 102.437 Earth years old on stardate 3842.4.</li>
      <li><span class="site-item">Fact:</span> The difference in time between stardate 43917.4 ("Sarek") and 3842.4 ("Journey to Babel") is approximately 100 years.</li>
    </ul>

